    <center><table class="itemDisplayTable">
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Title:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">A Project Report on Design and Fabrication of Sensor Based Inspection Conveyor</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Authors:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">N, Cibi chakravarthy<br />D.S, Mithun<br />S, Vasanthakumar</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Keywords:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">on Design and Fabrication<br />Sensor Based Inspection Conveyor</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Issue Date:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">1-May-2013 </td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Publisher:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">Srm University</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Series/Report no.:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">P6002</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Abstract:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue">In traditional manufacturing operations, a part is inspected after a machining operation and is either accepted, reworked or scrapped. The inspection step is often performed hours or even days after the machining step is completed. Sampling inspection techniques are used for parts produced in large lot size. Depending upon the nature of the part and the stability of the process used, these techniques virtually ensure the manufacture of defective parts. To avoid the defective parts, inspecting the material is necessary.
The machined components are transferred through the conveyor belt for subsequent operation. The sensors are used to measure the material dimensions and this signal is given to control Unit. The control unit gives the appropriate signal to the solenoid valve. The pneumatic cylinder is used to push the improper dimension materials. The inspection conveyor is very useful for material handling in modern engineering industries. The motor is used to drive the conveyor. The materials are moved from one place to another place by using conveyor. Sensors are used to measure the dimension. Inspection is carried out and the defective materials are pushed out by the single-acting cylinder.
This is a very efficient instrument for checking the dimensions like length, breadth, height etc., to be used in modern engineering industries. The manual efforts can be completely avoided by using this modern equipment. It also reduces the inspection time and manual inspection errors. If the work piece is defective, the pneumatic cylinder placed next to the sensor will be actuated to remove the defective work piece</td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">URI:&nbsp;</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17448">http://hdl.handle.net/123456789/17448</a></td></tr>
<tr><td class="metadataFieldLabel">Appears in Collections:</td><td class="metadataFieldValue"><a href="/dspace/handle/123456789/17020">Mech-2013</a><br/></td></tr>
</table></center><br/>
